---
description: >
  Wrapper that disables `fsync` and related calls by setting `LD_PRELOAD`
  before executing a given command. Installed by default on Ubuntu 26.04+
  (package `eatmydata`).
functions:
  command:
    - description: Execute a command. The `LD_PRELOAD` environment variable is set to load `libeatmydata.so`.
      code: eatmydata COMMAND
  shell:
    - description: Spawn a shell.
      code: eatmydata /bin/sh
  sudo:
    - description: If the binary is allowed to run as superuser by `sudo`, it does not drop the elevated privileges and may be used to access the file system, escalate or maintain privileged access.
      code: sudo eatmydata /bin/sh
  library-load:
    - description: >
        The tool sets `LD_PRELOAD=libeatmydata.so` before executing the
        command. A custom library can be injected by replacing
        `libeatmydata.so` on the library path.
      code: eatmydata COMMAND
---
